May 16 Casablanca Morocco - nine Moors - & black Arabs (3 hrs to desert) call to prayer on minaret - leather goods - (2 bags) French stores & cafes. Market & old quarter. snake  charmer   Sultans palace - harem - sweet peas - 
May 18 Lisbon - Portugal (?Radios?) from home & Jack to Bill  by the Tagus River & anchor at cobble wharf  with oblong basin full of colored wooden fishing slips with (unclear) masts  38 of them. (Unclear) could jump from one to the other. Market - crickets in cages - flowers -  Street cars to monastery & Tower of Belem dome of Estrella (& park) sprinkled slippery streets - next day Cintra XX castle ((unclear) plan) view of Moorish min  & sea - Town Hotel Nounes for lunch, strawberries & cream.  Moorish Palace new courts etc - Portugese Riviera a Sea -  Lovely sunset from deck.

Fri. May 25 - At Sea
First 2 days cold & gray. off Azores. Now mild & gray. (Kitty biting my paper. - Canary died & buried (not mine - but tried to cure it) Begin unclear - Bill reading unclear for unclear of church & how Peggy's "with us - this Present"   Reading French & Roman History  Finished "Vagabond" indicates out Bill's tea ?muffins?
June 3rd w/Romola after lunch Russ. unclear & Rum from 8 to 9 eves  New missionary doctor {[unclear]] & wife from Fez. Mrs. Henry Hinde - less nervous. Miss Morrow? serving refreshments to Capt'n & cribbage. Birds - jugs - trunk like mine & I finish unclear & 2 birds. ?wants? Kitty.

unclear way if on unclear hill among the Mts. Winding stream in valley - on which we embark in canoes to move if possible_ Saw mill & lovely water fall and long steep road up hill. Looks like a wild part of Berkshire hills. Telephone stop here at this house last unclear with St Felix telegraph and civilization. The real "jumping off" place. Russell + H got guides + canoes for tomorrow.  Packed in evening with all and their unclear + children sitting around the wall looking on. Mlle Caroline in fresh flowered Kimono in honor of occasion   Talked French. funny patois "etes vous fatze que?'

Aug 19th Monday.

  Finished packing.

Priest stayed in his tomb down cellar so did not dream. Watched guides seal joints in canoes. Noon-dinner- good bye to eggs and milk. Whole Menard family + all their friends came to bank of stream to see us off- just below the mill, red Japanese looking bridge and steep water fall. Four loaded canoes"sports" in bows ladies with air cushions and slat backs sitting tailor fashion, and I not- daring to move- four guides perched  on sterns kneeling with active paddlers. All 4 with paddles to use at will.

unload some- black flies awful- Passed old camp_ (muddy bank + log in water one) Riviere de Poste shot small rapids- climbed along steep side of impossible place on hands + knees. holding on to Howard_ hard work! Then got rested in lovely canoe trip up stream- a sunset_ second one on trip I believe) Blue herion flew angrily ahead. Camped at last dusk on high bank- meadow like place- open spot with golden rod + daisies _ Brought wood from opposite side of river for fire- had first venison for supper in the dark- lay on back + watched stars after supper. No boughs-  just bare ground!

August 31st Saturday - Cold & cloudy
Was cold without
bought - hot water bag
functioned before using y-
golden rod for head of bed
One week of gray weather
except - sunset -  light - last night -
Caribou for breakfast
paddled back to Manaurah
River and started downstream
in another direction-guides
promise better game-going
with current and welcomed 
us-easy work- Rapids
watched gregor & Oliver
bring carriers over - made
short stoney portage around
them-little rain-little
sun-light n. wind-
Blue herron went home this
A.M early-Trolled-

Sudden rain storm, nice oil coats- more lively rapids over & around boulder rocks- lunched on sandy bank- sun came out but = coole nap waiting for lunch- wooden cross by rapids for drowned fisherman- in afternoon passed fine rapids of La Croix Staid in canoe over some great fine exiting works- all safe- that was before the real La Croix ones - those were too lively and we portaged around waited looking up stream on big rocks with water swirling- cool drinks from dipper- beautiful portage through blue & raspberries & wild cherrys & all kinds of flowers- River most interesting all day.

saw bear & moose tracks fresh on the sand. and burned birch trees like lavender veils over the hills- impressionist views on all sides-  enjoys every minute & rapids most of all. Reach the Hills old camp where the Botted River enters Manawam and found it spoiled by other more recent campers- [crossed?] river to high bank in clear woods- sandy steep [unclear] mosquitos at first- [unclear] fish venison- fine dinner-- Heard moose. may find new camp to morrow- may stay here to explore Bottle River for Moose. lots of fresh trade- fine balsams

and darkness coming- Sudden crackling of hidden branches on H's side of river-  [unclear] bird notes coming toward their canoe-  His guide disappeared paddling swiftly behind wooded forest of land-  Prevort & I silent no [rain?] near other shore straining eye & ears-  then crack of branches and huge beast rushes into the stream out of sight of H & guide but aiming toward my  side of river right behind my canoe.  huge beast indeed seen swimming & splashing against the last rays of light up stream vanished in wood behind us. I shivered so I almost up set the canoe. - First

one I've seen- Exciting sport not sorry it got away- nor H. either I secretly guess-  Tea of Bologna sausage & toasted scones & mermalade in cozy tent= rain on  roof candle ight and books.  
Sep 4th Wednesday. Rained all night-  pouring now- Bad hunting- on account of weather-- even beasts stay at home.  Have lived in slickers and boots and for [unclear] comfort my [unclear] whistle which I have not needed to blow for man or beast.  Tent is water proof & comfy and seems like home-  H. & guides are getting breakfast in the down pour. My tent

business this time-  Prevort the talkative French Canadian left to take care of me-  Would prefer him gone too!-  Oiled my boots ( & whistle too) by camp fire-  Hatchet is left with me too always-  went down to bank in last dusk & washed handkerchief & nails with soap-  Looking up & down stream between [unclear] for dark shapes- saw things move in shrubbery a cross river but too dark to be sure-  they smell our camp fire- fresh tracks however right over there on sandy shore- of moose-deer caribou- bear & big gray wolf- Expect them all to arrive any minute.

great fire- like the novelty of sensation- Am now in tent with candle- Prevort's shadow between fire and side of tent looms large & weird-  Am writing by candle end- wind in tree tops-  fire crackling-  Sudden Shot- another it is dark now- so may be it got away then came a third so I guess he hit it-  If it runs I trust it will not crash out of woods directly into the back of this tent! Not a cheerful thought-  Draw the hatchet nearer! P.S. H. is back is not sure could not follow

worked hard on tree poem and wrote fresh 'Hunters Little boy" and Comforted-  Hatchet close by and whistle might scare beasts- beasts more afraid of humans however. Forgot to set to watch [unclear] & sky is all over gray so can't tell time and don't want to- Heard H. Whistle up stream & answered was just beginning to get hungry and collect dry wood when they appeared and strange to say they had been gone six hours instead of 4 or three & I did not feel [unclear] that it had been half the time and

not even felt hungry or lonely once.  H. glad to see me-  He & Russell had been fishing & he brought string of Brook trout and Russel sent some Beaver- glad he found different sport there makes it interesting- sorry I did not feel like going too-  Trout for supper- rich pink meat good- wore bandana for mosquitoes & sat by fire on bench H. made and heard Oliver tell of his experiences as trapper in the cold winter- also bear story- must be lovely in winter I went to bed & listened to H. & guides by fire- Comfy!

Long Lake trip which was what Oliver referred to . Last night in permanent camp . Warm [unclear]
Sep 8th Sunday
Till 2 a.m. Provort noisy in tent. (?) drink?
Beautiful day- First in two weeks now we are leaving!  warm enough to go swimming too! Have not  taken bathing suit out of bag.  Soft air mist rising- are packing up to go to Rapids of La Croix with our stuff and guides who will then be able to help the Hills over that portage with their stuff-  They will make an early start and join us at La Croix for luncheon then up stream we go and

it wont be as easy as coming down- as Oliver is fond of saying most seriously and respectfully "all right coming down but going up- we catch H_ _!" We enjoyed wandering about the portage & rapids while the Hills were coming- If the hunting were better there it couldn't be a prettier spot for a camp. near where the wooden cross stands up against the sky.  A perfect morning as good as being at church for the Sunday feeling- that "Sunday feeling" grows on one in the wilds- little worries can't stay- it's good for

My miraculous Biscuit-
1 2/3 cups flour           [bracket 3 ingredients]
1/2 Tsp. salt                    Mix together
2 Tsp. baking powder 
Table sp. full Lard  ) rub in well with spoon
cup + of water  ) add slowly
Roll out on floured oil cloth with the Worcestershire sauce bottle and bake in tin reflecting oven close to camp fire.
Be sure cork of W. bottle is in tight!

Thursday
My dear Mrs. Shaw—
Card of the Hotel de Loudres [unclear] dei [unclear] which I so  highly recommend, and especially the manager Michele Albano, of whom my husband and I are very fond.

you may not like it, for it is both fanciful and disagreeable, but it did give me a [unclear] picture and the feeling I so often have in Italy that their pagan ancestors are not forgotten-

I'm sorry I cannot remember the name of the book about Russia by Dorothy Thompson and apparently it has disappeared from my shelves --Hoping you may like these books as well as I do believe [unclear],  Faithfully Yours

Mary Slaughter Fried
